==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cleopatras needle
<hw>Cle`o*pa"tra's nee"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[So named after
<etsep>Cleopatra</etsep>, queen of Egypt.]</ety> <def>Either of two
obelisks which were moved in ancient times from Heliopolis to
Alexandria, one of which is now on the Thames Embankment in London, and
the other in Central Park, in the City of New York.</def></p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Some writers consider that only the obelisk now in
Central Park is properly called <ex>Cleopatra's needle</ex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clench</ent>⟦br⟧
